            <h2>Project Overview</h2>
            <p>
                This portfolio demonstrates a production-ready data pipeline that mirrors the academic research workflows 
                used by platforms like Wharton Research Data Services (WRDS). The project showcases end-to-end ETL 
                (Extract-Transform-Load) capabilities, database management, analytics processing, and automated testingâ€”all 
                with a focus on reproducibility, data integrity, and operational excellence.
            </p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <strong>Technical Leadership Demonstrated:</strong> This project reflects the same principles required for 
                managing a data engineering team: architecting scalable pipelines, implementing version-controlled transformations, 
                ensuring data quality, documenting processes for reproducibility, and establishing CI/CD best practices.
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Core Competencies Demonstrated</h2>
